cquisition in december the line of credit balance was reduced to  last week repaid from the proceeds of reit shares sold but we are about to dip into the line again to purchase our next asset a consequence of our buyfirst sell reit sharesnext strategy is that the reit built up depreciation deductions in  that fully “tax sheltered” the dividends that were paid to shareholders these depreciation deductions have reduced your tax or “cost” basis in your reit shares investment and under current irs codes you will be taxed at capital gains rates on the difference between your ultimate sales price of your reit shares and your cost basis we trust that this clarifies any misunderstanding that you may have had it is important to note that no reit share offering proceeds were used to pay dividends all dividend were paid from property rental receipts replyget me out saysmarch rd  at  amyou are so full of crap any “paper” depreciation at this time will subject the holder to hell of a liability when the underlying properties are sold or disposed of you are liar and a crook and amazing how  other “ star” reviews showed up within hours of your posting i can’t wait to see you in prison where your anus will be turned into cole slaw rating    ryan hirsch says february th  at  am not sure what everyone is so upset about if you speak to your accountant they will be able to explain how the  is read i’ve received mine from them and everything checks out reply rating    marina says february th  at  am i’m not sure where all these comments are coming from i’ve been an investor since october and live this investment…dividend have been exactly as expected and my accountant explained the  to me just as described by customer service…i’m moving some dollars from my k next replyget me out saysmarch th  at  amlol is that you under the skirt howard one of your sock puppets that all mysteriously sprang up within minutes of your post marina saysmarch th  at  pmdon’t want to sell my shares i like the 