imbursements to advisory intermediaries typically the sponsor of a nonexchange listed public reit such as rich uncles enlists the sales expertise of an inhouse dealermanager responsible for marketing shares in a reit in compensation the brokerdealer or financial intermediary usually receives up to  of investments made in the reit as commissions or cost reimbursements in fashioning an alternative funding scheme rich uncles believes its real estate investment vehicle delivers roughly  more of the investment amount to acquire the actual real estate rather than in the form of commissions and reimbursements the reit expects to use a substantial amount of the net proceeds from the upcoming public offering to invest in singletenant incomeproducing corporate properties hofer and wirta have a history of trying to open up cre deals to smaller investors the pair previously sponsored two reits nexregen firewheel real estate investment trust in  a singleasset reit that offered to invest in a limited partnership that owned a shopping center in garland tx more recently the pair organized rich uncles real estate investment trust i in  to invest in singletenant properties in california both offerings used wirta’s and hofer’s proprietary webbased system that pools smalldollar interests made by individual investors to buy commercial properties get in touch        contact costar news team   newscostarcom more us national newsback to us national news pageecommerce comes to food shopping amazonwhole foods combination seen as gamechanger for grocery storesecommerce comes to food shopping growing competition for grocery sales altering outlook for retail real estateblackstone to spinoff la quinta’s hotels into a new reitapple iphone supplier to build  billion plant in wisconsinglobal wave of office overbuilding could add shine to us markets for investorshas us lodging sectors historic growth run finally reached a tipping pointequity commonwealth closes on m sale of centre square east  west 